race.comment: The likelihood of a hot tempo brings COSMONOVA (18) right under notice at good odds. Went back from a wide alley then flew late to get up for third in the Group 3 Mona Lisa over 1350m at Wyong last start. Better placed on this bigger track. Can storm home late under the light weight. KERGUELEN (10) was in commission as usual last time out and did a good job to get up for a close third after conceding plenty of ground on the bend in a BM88 over 1100m at Rosehill. Has won three from four at today's trip so with luck from the gate he is a big danger. GETAFIX (9) draws perfectly and is in the mix first-up on the back of two solid trials. BOSTON ROCKS (12) needed the run last time and can improve sharply back on top of the ground.
